# IPAdapter Settings

# Weight - Controls the influence of the provided image toward the generation, traditionally the higher the number the more influence.

# Noise - An interesting settings, lower settings leads to MORE noise supplied. Higher value leads to LESS noise. The amount of noise present affects the conditioning of the generation. Mess around with this to get it were you like it.

# Weight Type -
 
--# Original : Makes the Weight value work as expected. Higher value leads to stronger influence

--# Linear : Works similar to Original, but is weaker in influence.

--# Channel Penalty : Creates a sharper generated image. Github page suggests values > 1 work well with it

# Timestep - Decide when in the generation you would want the influence present. Play with it to see how you like the results.

# Faceid_v2, weight_v2, unfold_batch - They aren't really used in this workflow and don't affect anything that I've seen when using this.

# FreeU
If you want to look at what this does actually, the github page is https://github.com/ChenyangSi/FreeU

TLDR is that it improves upon your generation by merging different features during denoising process.

Definitely play with these settings to see what applies to you most.

The settings I'm using are after I mass-tested a buncha different settings until I liked the changes.
